Participants at UNICEF’s Child Friendly Community Initiative (CFCI), have advocated for establishing taskforce in Adamawa state. The resolution was made known, at one-day state inception meeting in Yola, led by the Chief of Field Office Bauchi, Mr Bhanu Pathak. The presumed objective is to strengthen the CFCI implementation in state, LGA and existing 6 communities, towards scaling up modalities in the 2020 agreed terms of reference. The state planning commission anticipated to be the coordinating agency participants urged for operational funding support from the state government. The funds would be for monitoring of community intervention and logistics for project implementation at local government levels. The meeting also stressed the need adopt child-centered attitudes, behavior and practice and improve access to basic services that promote child well-being and development. Participants drawn from relevant MDAs, state, agreed that, the pilot projects be implemented in Guyuk and Fofure LGAs of the state. 